gomodel:SYNGO_3843  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Loss of NETO1 leads to impaired GluK1c delivery to distal axons\"\n\nFig.4: \"NETO1 is required for tonic activity of KARs at CA3-CA1 synapse in the neonatal hippocampus\"\n\nFig.5: \"NETO1 deficiency leads to loss of functional presynaptic KARs at immature CA3-CA1 synapses that is rescued with GluK1c overexpression in the area CA3\"\n\n9/7/2018 Pim\n- The data shows that there are less KARs at the presynaptic membrane (ePhys). Since the authors claim that the trafficking of the KARs into the axon is perturbed in Neto1-/- neurons, I have considered the reduced amounts of the NT receptor at the presynaptic membrane (term 'regulation of presynaptic membrane neurotransmitter receptor levels') as secondary and I decided not to make this annotation for Neto1.. Experimental description: - \"Experiments were performed using wild-type (WT), Neto1 -/-, and Neto2 -/- (C57Bl/6NCrl) mice\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-10-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3843" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

